Question Text:
Examine the following show command output on a router configured for dynamic NAT:
"â€” Inside Source
access-list 1 pool examsdigest
pool examsdigest: netmask 255.255.255.240
start 190.1.1.1 end 190.1.1.10
type generic, total addresses 10, allocated 10 (100%), misses 595"
You are responsible to find out why users are not being able to reach the Internet.
Choices:
a. The cause is not related to dynamic NAT
b. The command output does not provide any clue to identify the problem
c. Dynamic NAT can't use Standard ACLs
d. The NAT pool does not have enough entries to fulfill the user's requests
LLM Explanation: The output shows that the NAT pool 'examsdigest' has a total of 10 addresses available, and all 10 have been allocated (100% utilization). Additionally, there have been 595 misses, meaning there were 595 attempts to allocate an address from the pool when no addresses were available. This indicates that the NAT pool is exhausted and does not have enough entries to fulfill all the user requests, preventing some users from reaching the Internet.
URLs: ['Cisco CCNA Official Cert Guide, Chapter 10: Network Address Translation', 'Cisco Documentation: Configuring Dynamic NAT - https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/ios-xml/ios/ipaddr_nat/configuration/15-mt/nat-15-mt-book/iadnat-addr-consv.html']

Question Text: Log messages may tell you about some events, either critical or not. To help you make sense of the importance of each message, IOS assigns each message a severity level. Which of the following severity level means Warning - Warning condition?
LLM Explanation: In Cisco IOS, severity level 4 corresponds to warning messages. These messages indicate a warning condition that should be monitored and addressed to prevent issues. Severity levels range from 0 to 7, with 0 being the most severe (emergency) and 7 being the least severe (debugging).
URLs: ['Cisco IOS Configuration Fundamentals Command Reference: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/ios-xml/ios/fundamentals/command/Cisco_IOS_Configuration_Fundamentals_Command_Reference.html', 'Cisco IOS System Error Messages: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/docs/ip/open-shortest-path-first-ospf/200186-Cisco-IOS-System-Error-Messages.html']

Question Text: Log messages may tell you about some events, either critical or not. To help you make sense of the importance of each message, IOS assigns each message a severity level. Which of the following severity level means Informational: Informational message only?
LLM Explanation: Severity level 6 corresponds to informational messages in Cisco IOS. These messages are not errors, but rather provide information about system events and status for reference. Severity level 1 indicates the highest severity (alerts), while 4 and 5 represent warning and notification levels respectively.
URLs: ['Cisco IOS Configuration Fundamentals Command Reference: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/ios-xml/ios/fundamentals/command/Cisco_IOS_Configuration_Fundamentals_Command_Reference.html', 'Cisco IOS System Error Messages: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/docs/dial-access/integrated-services-digital-networks-isdn-channel-associated-signaling-cas/10374-syslog.html']

Question Text: One of the features of SNMPv3 is called message integrity.
LLM Explanation: Message integrity is indeed one of the key features introduced in SNMPv3. It ensures that SNMP messages have not been altered or corrupted in transit by using authentication mechanisms like HMAC-MD5 or HMAC-SHA. This provides protection against tampering and unauthorized modifications to the SNMP messages.
URLs: ['CCNA 200-301 Official Cert Guide, Volume 1 by Wendell Odom', 'Network Management Fundamentals by Alexander Clemm', 'RFC 3414 - User-based Security Model (USM) for version 3 of the Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMPv3)']

Question Text: You have been tasked to find out whether the Cisco Discovery Protocol (CDP) is enabled globally. Which command will you type?
Choices:
a. show protocols
b. show cdp
c. show running-config
d. show interface brief
LLM Explanation: The 'show cdp' command is used to display information about the Cisco Discovery Protocol (CDP) configuration and status on a Cisco device. This command will show whether CDP is enabled globally, as well as other CDP-related information such as the CDP timer, holdtime, and the interfaces on which CDP is enabled.
URLs: ['Cisco IOS Network Management Command Reference: https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/ios-xml/ios/netmgmt/command/nm-cr-book/nm-s1.html#wp3351083440', 'Cisco Networking Academy - Introduction to Networks v7.0 (ITN) - Chapter 11: Build a Small Network']

Question Text: Which of the following protocols synchronize the time of different systems?
Choices:
a. NTP
b. SMTP
c. UDP
d. CDP
LLM Explanation: NTP (Network Time Protocol) is used to synchronize the clocks of computer systems over packet-switched, variable-latency data networks. It allows network devices to maintain accurate timekeeping by periodically querying a set of servers that provide a highly accurate time source. SMTP is used for email, UDP is a transport protocol, and CDP is a Cisco proprietary protocol for device discovery, none of which are used for time synchronization.
URLs: ['CCNA 200-301 Official Cert Guide, Wendell Odom, Cisco Press', 'Network Time Protocol (NTP) General Overview, Cisco Documentation']

Question Text: R1 and R2 are attached to the same Ethernet VLAN, with subnet 192.168.1.0/24, and addresses 192.168.1.1, 192.168.2 respectively. The routers use an FHRP. Host A and host B attach to the same LAN and have correct default router settings per the FHRP configuration. Which of the following statements is true for this LAN?
Choices:
a. You can't connect two routers to the same LAN subnet.
b. If one router fails, hosts can't send packets off-subnet
c. If one router fails, both hosts will use the one remaining router as a default router
d. if one router fails, only one of the two hosts will still be able to send packets off-subnet
LLM Explanation: In a LAN with two routers using a First Hop Redundancy Protocol (FHRP) like HSRP or VRRP, if one router fails, the other router will take over as the active router. All hosts on the LAN will then use the remaining router as their default gateway to send packets off-subnet. The FHRP ensures that there is always an active router available to forward traffic, providing redundancy and preventing a single point of failure.
URLs: ['Cisco CCNA 200-301 Official Cert Guide, Volume 1, Chapter 16: First Hop Redundancy Protocol', 'https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/docs/ip/hot-standby-router-protocol-hsrp/9234-hsrpguidetoc.html']

Question Text: Which of the following characteristics of network traffic can be managed by Quality of Service (QoS)? (Choose all that apply)
Choices:
a. Bandwidth
b. LLQ
c. Loss
d. Delay
e. CoS
f. Jitter
LLM Explanation: Quality of Service (QoS) is a set of technologies that work on a network to guarantee its ability to dependably run high-priority applications and traffic under limited network capacity. QoS can manage bandwidth allocation, packet loss, delay (or latency), and jitter (variations in delay). Low Latency Queuing (LLQ) and Class of Service (CoS) are QoS mechanisms or tools rather than characteristics of network traffic.
URLs: ['Cisco Networking Academy: Introduction to Networks v7.0 (ITN)', 'Cisco Press CCNA 200-301 Official Cert Guide, Volume 1 by Wendell Odom']
